08 Jan 2013 13:21






The containment procedures mention that no one is allowed to tap on the window, and the [DATA EXPUNGED]s in the story of how the window came into the Foundation's possession imply something dramatic happening, but neither of those things are fleshed out, and the article is, as previous comments have agreed, severely underwhelming as a result. All two or three minutes I spent reading this article, I was waiting for at least one of those two points to be elaborated on, and I was very much let down when they weren't.

In short, the idea has some potential - even if it isn't terribly original - but the way it is, as far as I'm concerned, the article fails. Downvoted.







